                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I apprechiate your response Amerie Robeseeker, and I still disagree. Essentially there are a couple important differences between your case and this one. Firstly, you didn't kill anyone and the petition specifically talks about when a fatality is involved and someone dies. Most people aren't going to kill someone with a failure to stop, and in fact rear end collisions are the most common accident on the road today so vehicles are designed with that in mind. 
<br />

<br />
Compare that to a commercial driver who's vehicle is significantly more dangerous then the average car.  Not only are they generally traveling at higher speeds but they're essentially driving a tank. It's a much more powerful piece of equipment and with more power comes more responsibility and higher expectations. I don't think it's unreasonable to expect more from commercial drivers then regular drivers at all. 
<br />

<br />
Lets consider for comparision an old job I had at Mr. Lube. One day during a busy Saturday afternoon I accidentally forgot to put oil back into a vehicle before letting it go. The fellow got about 5 blocks and started wondering why his oil light was on so called us back. My manager drove over, found the vechicle was completely dry and filled it up with oil. No damage was done to the car, but I think it's fair to say we lost a customer for good that day. Naturally, I was fired for it. 
<br />

<br />
Now here is a situation where someone through their negligence (they were at fault after all, that's why they were fined) killed another person. Isn't it reasonable for that person to lose their job for killing someone? If someone has demonstrated they are a danger to others isn't it time to get them off the road before they hurt someone else? My step-father has been a truck driver for 17 years, and has never had an accident. He works exclusively long haul jobs and in fact, of the 20 some employees they've had no one has ever been killed or even seriously injured by one of their workers. A fender bender at a stop sign in city between casual drivers is one thing, but completely crushing another human being while at work is in a different class entirely.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />When a government has ceased to protect the lives, liberty and property of the people, from whom its legitimate powers are derived, and for the advancement of whose happiness it was instituted, and so far from being a guarantee for the enjoyment of those inestimable and inalienable rights, becomes an instrument in the hands of evil rulers for their oppression. - Declaration of Independence of the State of Texas.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
