                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First of all, I find it incredibly hard to believe that the driver of the truck only 'got away with a $75 fine'. At the very minimum, someone would have filed an insurance claim, even if it was only him. An accident of that magnitude would have increased his premiums to an outragous amount. Also, any moving violation against a CDL requires at minimum a retake of the CDL tests, and, most likely resulted in a loss of the CDL instead. The company he drove for was, most likely, responsible for the accident financially (insurance wise) and most likely, he was fired, or at the very minimum, taken off the road. Also, I find it hard to believe that he was not at least investigated for vehicular manslaughter (or some variant of it).  The only way that he wouldn't be found guilty of that is if the road conditions were such that no amount of caution would have prevented the accident. 
<br />

<br />
Case in point, I was involved in an accident once where a driver of a pickup truck had been carrying a 5 gallon can of kerosene, his tailgate was down, and when he left off from a stoplight, the can fell off the back and spilled across the lane. Several cars had passed through this area, and the can, and its contents, were spread across the whole lane. When I arrived shortly after, I went to turn into a fast food place just short of the intersection, and when I hit the brakes, I began sliding, and continued sliding into the back of another car. The driver of the pickup who was carrying the can of kerosene was never identified (the real person to blame), and everyone involved in the pileup was given a 'no fault' ticket (no traffic violation was awarded anyone). However, since this particular driver WAS awarded a failure to stop ticket, this type of situation was not the case.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, to say he got away with only a $75 fine is very unlikely.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">That is all I have to say about that! - Forest Gump</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
